node_modules/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security assessment output — IGNORED BY DEFAULT (secure-by-default)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Threat reports contain sensitive vulnerability details, attack vectors, CWE
# evidence with file+line references, and architecture weaknesses. Committing
# them into version control exposes an attacker's roadmap — even in private
# repos (accidental public visibility, insider threats, credential rotation).
#
# To opt in (private repo, controlled access, policy permits it):
#   1. Remove or comment out the "docs/security/" line below.
#   2. Keep "docs/security/pentest-tasks.yaml" ignored unless you have a
#      specific need — it lists concrete probe targets.
#   3. Consider adding docs/security/ to CODEOWNERS with restricted access.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs/security/
# Same artefacts when a script is invoked from inside scripts/ and writes a
# relative docs/security/ path — never track those either.
scripts/docs/
# Same artefacts when the analyzed repo is nested inside this repo, for example
# during local fixture or E2E runs.
**/docs/security/
# Manual full-run E2E driver writes artifacts here. Same threat-data
# sensitivity rationale as docs/security/ above — never commit.
tests/fixtures/e2e/_last-run/
tests/fixtures/e2e/_last-run-req/
# QA-active repair variant (run-repair.sh) — `rm -rf` + `cp` regenerated
# scratch dir, run with --keep-runtime-files. Never commit.
tests/fixtures/e2e/_repair-run/
# eval-threat-model skill working dir (brief + judge/verify sidecars +
# EVAL-REVIEW.md). Same threat-data sensitivity rationale — never commit.
.eval-out/

# AppSec runtime state (live progress / in-flight status snapshots)
.appsec-progress.json

# Persistent caches (auto-created at runtime)
.cache/
data/appsec-requirements-fallback.yaml

